  "texts": [
    "In general, there is a positive correlation between latency and FLOPs.",
    "This is because more FLOPs typically lead to more complex computations, which can increase the processing time.",
    "Our proposed MCAP method achieved low latency while having relatively high FLOPs.",
    "This is mainly due to the specific focus of the MCAP being on optimizing the inference latency by reducing the number of computations and parameters required for each layer, while still maintaining sufficient accuracy.",
    "This results in a higher FLOP count compared to methods that focus more on accuracy-efficiency trade-offs.To comprehensively evaluate the model, we considered other parameters such as MCC (Matthews Correlation Coefficient), average loss and also model's latency."
  ],
